<TITLE> Basundhara Group chairman, family face arrest orders </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 25 (bdnews24.com)  A Dhaka court Wednesday issued warrants of arrest against Basundhara Group chairman Ahmed Akbar Sobhan, his wife, sons and two officials of the company for dodging tax. The Senior Special Judge's Court in Dhaka issued the orders after the National Board of Revenue filed a case against the seven people and Basundhara Industrial Complex Limited for dodging about Tk 8.27 crore in tax. Judge Azizul Haque asked the authorities to submit a report on the warrants to the court on July 31. Basundhara Industrial Complex Limited, a subsidiary of Basundhara Group, has been made the main accused in the case. The other accused are Sobhan's wife Afroza Begum, also director of the group, sons Sadaat Sobhan, Safayet Sobhan and Sayem Sobhan and deputy managing director Mostafizur Rahman and accountant MM Quddus of the company. According to case details, the accused dodged taxes for 2004-2007. bdnew
